FAISAL II OF IRAQ TO ARRIVE TODAY; 17-Year-Old King, on His First Trip Here, Will Tour U. S. and Visit the President

Aug. 12, 1952

Full text is unavailable for this digitized archive article. Subscribers may view the full text of this article in its original form through TimesMachine.

King Faisal II of Iraq, with his royal entourage including Emir Regent Abdul Illah, will arrive here at 11 A. M. today aboard the Cunard liner Queen Mary for an informal visit to the United States until Sept. 10. This will be the 17-year-old monarch's first visit to this country.
